# Shopify Section Usage Guide

This guide explains how to edit the following sections in Shopify Theme Editor:

1. Split Hero & Features
2. Hero Slideshow Header
3. Hers Labs Hero
4. Shop Color Grid
5. Product Glass Card
6. Center Product Carousel
7. Clickable Lookbook
8. Hex Prism Carousel
9. Footer

All settings listed here are currently functional.

---

## 1) Split Hero & Features
Section file: `sections/split-hero-features.liquid`

### What this section is for
A top hero area (background/image/text/buttons), followed by a feature grid, with optional disclaimer content.

### Main editable components in Shopify
- `Heading` (`top_heading`): Main hero heading. Use `|` to split lines.
- `Heading Size` / `Heading Weight`: Typography of hero heading.
- `Primary Button Text/URL`, `Secondary Button Text/URL`: Hero CTAs.
- `Button Location`, `Button Vertical Position`, `Button Vertical Offset`: CTA placement.
- Button styles: radius, size (desktop/mobile), glassy toggles, color and hover color settings.
- `Top Background Type` + `Top Background Image` or `Top Background Gradient`.
- `Top Logo`: Optional text/SVG HTML logo area.
- `Center Image`, `Center Image Height`, Y offsets desktop/mobile.
- Center text group: above/overlap text, size, weight, color, vertical offsets.
- Bottom area colors/gradients and bottom padding.
- Mobile feature scaling controls (`mobile_*` settings).
- `Features Layout`, `Features Container Width`, `Section Border Radius`, `Enable full width layout`.
- Disclaimer controls: HTML + read more/read less labels + collapsed height.

### Block components
Block type: `Feature Box`
- Image/icon, title, descriptions.
- Optional per-feature button + style/colors.
- Typography (title/description size and weight).
- Image placement and sizing controls.
- Middle-layout text controls.
- Box width/height and color overrides.
- Animation type/speed/easing/delay.

### Usage notes
- Add exactly the number of `Feature Box` blocks you need; then choose matching `Features Layout`.
- Use mobile scaling settings for small laptop/mobile consistency.
- If disclaimer text is long, keep a short `Read More Label`.

